 and an integrated service library make it easy to model new or existing, simple or complex applications in a way that is cloud agnostic. CloudCenter delivers a full lifecycle approach to deploying and managing applications on any cloud. CloudCenter is carefully designed to optimize work streams and provide users with the power of self-service, on demand deployment, while minimizing the need to understand nuances of the underlying cloud environment. As seen in the figure below, the approach includes three phases that empower users to quickly and easily model, deploy, and manage application stacks on demand. It also gives administrators enterprise class visibility and governance control across boundaries of applications, clouds, and users.\r\nCloudCenter offers exceptional multitenant management capabilities that deliver complete isolation for peer tenants, partial isolation for parent-child tenants, and flexible sharing options for users within a tenant. With an enterprise-class multitenant solution, IT can avoid the need to deploy multiple management tools for multiple tenants. At the same time, IT can simplify and reduce its service delivery footprint and can gain central governance capabilities that cross the boundaries of applications, clouds, and users. The Cisco CloudCenter solution delivers multitenant capabilities that are powerful enough for many cloud service providers that deliver hybrid cloud services to fully isolated customers. Yet the solution is also simple enough for enterprise IT to configure a variety of deployment models to meet the isolation and sharing needs of any organization, simple or complex. This lab covers basic installation and configuration of CloudCenter, and is an introduction to unified administration and governance.\r\n\r\nDescription The CloudCenter QuickStart Mentored Installation is a four day onsite, mentored installation designed to assist customers with rapid deployment of CloudCenter. The engagement combines training in conjunction with initial design, review and preparation of the customer’s existing infrastructure, installation, and deployment of an operational CloudCenter solution. The intended audience is IT personnel who need deployment services and a well-defined knowledge transfer.\r\n</p>[/fusion_text][fusion_imageframe image_id="110" style_type="bottomshadow" stylecolor="#424242" hover_type="none" bordersize="" bordercolor="" borderradius="" align="center" lightbox="no" gallery_id="" lightbox_image="" alt="" link="" linktarget="_self" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="cloud-center-img" id="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset=""]https://www.webpioneersolutions.com/webapp/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/unnamed.png[/fusion_imageframe][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container][fusion_builder_container hundred_percent="no" hundred_percent_height="no" hundred_percent_height_scroll="no" hundred_percent_height_center_content="yes" equal_height_columns="no" menu_anchor="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="center center" background_repeat="no-repeat" fade="no" background_parallax="none" enable_mobile="no" parallax_speed="0.3" video_mp4="" video_webm="" video_ogv="" video_url="" video_aspect_ratio="16:9" video_loop="yes" video_mute="yes" video_preview_image="" border_size="" border_color="" border_style="solid" margin_top="" margin_bottom="" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left=""][fusion_builder_row][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left="" dimension_margin="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Overall Objectives</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Collaborate with key personnel to determine functionality goals.</li>\r\n 	<li>High-level discovery of existing Private and Public Cloud requirements, servers, and applications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Interactive training, design, and implementation sessions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Migration strategy and planning.</li>\r\n 	<li>Implementation of CloudCenter\r\n<ul>\r\n         <li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n 	<li>Launch the CloudCenter Manager (CCM) Appliance</li>\r\n 	<li>Launch the Monitor Appliance</li>\r\n 	<li>Launch the RabbitMQ Appliance</li>\r\n 	<li>Launch the CloudCenter Orchestrator (CCO) Appliance</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring CloudCenter</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring a Cloud</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring Users</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring Tenants</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring Applications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left="" dimension_margin="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Training Objectives:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="list-style-type: none;">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Discussing the Architecture of CloudCenter</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuration of CloudCenter and its Components</li>\r\n 	<li>Administering CloudCenter</li>\r\n 	<li>App Modeling and Deployment</li>\r\n 	<li>Reporting and Governance</li>\r\n 	<li>Application Management</li>\r\n 	<li>Managing Using AWS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_1" layout="1_1" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left="" dimension_margin="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<span>Implementation:</san>The CloudCenter QuickStart involves establishing the requirements and Deploying the CloudCenter and Migrating Applications and Integrating with Private and Public Cloud Environments.[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container][fusion_builder_container hundred_percent="no" hundred_percent_height="no" hundred_percent_height_scroll="no" hundred_percent_height_center_content="yes" equal_height_columns="no" menu_anchor="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="center center" background_repeat="no-repeat" fade="no" background_parallax="none" enable_mobile="no" parallax_speed="0.3" video_mp4="" video_webm="" video_ogv="" video_url="" video_aspect_ratio="16:9" video_loop="yes" video_mute="yes" video_preview_image="" border_size="" border_color="" border_style="solid" margin_top="" margin_bottom="" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left=""][fusion_builder_row][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left="" dimension_margin="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 1 - Morning</h4>\r\n    <ul>\r\n       <li>Customer Current and future Cloud requirements</li>\r\n       <li><b>White Board session 1 - </b> Benefits of CloudCenter and discussing some CloudCenter use cases based on the Customer Requirements.</li>\r\n       <li><b>White Board Session 2 – </b> Discussing CloudCenter Components and Architecture, High Availability\r\n</li>\r\n   </ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 1 - Afternoon </h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Hands on Session - Deploying OVA CloudCenter and its Components</li>\r\n 	    <ul>\r\n               <li>Deploy CCM OVA in vCenter</li>\r\n               <li>Deploy Cloud Center Health Monitor Virtual Appliance</li>\r\n               <li>Deploy RabbitMQ Virtual Appliance for vSphere</li>\r\n               <li>Deploy CCO Virtual Appliance for vSphere</li>\r\n               <li>Deploy Cloud Center Repository Virtual Appliance</li>\r\n               <li>Deploy Cloud Center Worker VM Virtual Appliance</li>\r\n               <li>Modify VM Properties</li>\r\n\r\n            </ul>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 2 - Morning</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Whiteboard Session 3 –</b> Discussing CloudCenter Components and their Functions.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Hands on Session -</b> Configuration\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Configure CloudCenter Manager</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Cloud Center Monitor Virtual Appliance</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure RabbitMQ for vSphere</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Cloud Center Orchestrator for vSphere</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Cloud Center Repo VM</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare vSphere Template Environment for Cloud Center</li>\r\n 	<li>Verify the Installation</li>\r\n 	<li>Configuring Cloud Center Regions</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Cloud Infrastructure for vSphere Private Cloud</li>\r\n 	<li>Map Images for the Private Cloud</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 2 - Afternoon</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Whiteboard Session 4 –</b> Administering CloudCenter. Discussing Work Flow, Users, group &amp; roles, Usage &amp; Fees, Creating Deployment Environment</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Hands on Session -</b> Administration\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Configure Tenant Information</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Bundles, Usage Plans, and Contracts</li>\r\n 	<li>Create Deployment Environments</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Activation Profiles</li>\r\n 	<li>Configure Cloud Center Users, Groups, and Roles</li>\r\n 	<li>Assign Contracts and Usage Plans to Users</li>\r\n 	<li>Customize A Deployment Environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 3 - Morning</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Whiteboard session 5 – </b>Modeling Application, Running Apps on vSphere.</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Hands on Session - </b>Application Modelling\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Modeling and Deploying Applications</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the Repository to Cloud Center</li>\r\n 	<li>Model a Simple One-Tier Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Deploy a Simple Application into vSphere</li>\r\n 	<li>Model a Multi-Tier Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Deploy a Multi-Tier Application into vSphere</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type="1_2" layout="1_2" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 3 - Afternoon</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Whiteboard Session 6 –</b> Discussion on Governance and Reporting</li>\r\n 	<li><b>Hands on Session -</b> Cloud Center Reporting and Governance\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>View Cloud Center Reports</li>\r\n 	<li>View Deployment Details</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitor Deployment Virtual Machines</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and Use System Tags</li>\r\n 	<li>Create and Use Cloud Center Policies</li>\r\n 	<li>Implement Cloud Center Governance and Policies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container][fusion_builder_container hundred_percent="no" hundred_percent_height="no" hundred_percent_height_scroll="no" hundred_percent_height_center_content="yes" equal_height_columns="no" menu_anchor="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="center center" background_repeat="no-repeat" fade="no" background_parallax="none" enable_mobile="no" parallax_speed="0.3" video_mp4="" video_webm="" video_ogv="" video_url="" video_aspect_ratio="16:9" video_loop="yes" video_mute="yes" video_preview_image="" border_size="" border_color="" border_style="solid" margin_top="" margin_bottom="" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left=""][fusion_builder_row][fusion_builder_column type="1_1" layout="1_1" spacing="" center_content="no" link="" target="_self" min_height="" hide_on_mobile="small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility" class="" id="" background_color="" background_image="" background_position="left top" background_repeat="no-repeat" hover_type="none" border_size="0" border_color="" border_style="solid" border_position="all" padding_top="" padding_right="" padding_bottom="" padding_left="" dimension_margin="" animation_type="" animation_direction="left" animation_speed="0.3" animation_offset="" last="no"][fusion_text]<h4>Day 4 – Full Day</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n    \r\n     <li><b>Whiteboard Session -</b> Discussion on requirements for integrating with Public Cloud</li>\r\n     <li><b>Hands on Session -</b> Managing AWS Cloud Using Cloud Center</li>\r\n       <ul>	\r\n        <li>Create AWS Security Groups for Cloud Center Nodes</li>	\r\n        <li>Create AWS Key Pair for Cloud Center Nodes</li>	\r\n        <li>Deploy Rabbit-AMQP instance on Amazon Web Services</li>\r\n        <li>Deploy CCO instance on Amazon Web Services</li>	\r\n        <li>Configure AWS - Rabbit-AMQP Instance for Cloud Center Manager</li>	\r\n        <li>Configure AWS - Cloud Center Orchestrator Instance for Cloud Center Manager	</li>\r\n        <li>Configure Cloud Center Regions: Define Clouds, Cloud Accounts, and Regions</li>\r\n        <li>Associate AWS to Deployment Environments</li>	\r\n        <li>Apply System Tags to Deployment Environments</li>	\r\n        <li>Deploy an Application to AWS</li>	\r\n        <li>Migrate an Application from AWS to vSphere</li>\r\n     </ul>\r\n</ul>[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container]', 'Cloud Center', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '105-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-04-11 13:47:54', '2018-04-11 13:47:54', '', 105, 'https://www.webpioneersolutions.com/webapp/105-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
